This shapefile represents a subset of GEOSAM (Iowa's Geologic Sampling Points) that has geologic data associated with site specific data that may consist of well samples, cores, quarry faces, roadcuts, or river exposures.</abstract>    <purpose>To be utilized as a point source for geologic interpretations of Iowa geology (both structure and thickness).</purpose>    <supplinf>This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources.</supplinf>    <langdata Sync="TRUE">en</langdata></descript>   <timeperd>    <timeinfo>     <sngdate>      <caldate>20120322</caldate>     </sngdate>    </timeinfo>    <current>edition Because of the nature of stratigraphic data multiple records per site location are created that then can be filtered by any combination or individually of geologic System, Group, Formation, or Member.  Primary, secondary, and tertiary lithologies are also noted and can be filtered against also.
